The Computer Professional Registration Council of Nigeria (CPN) yesteday described unregistered practitioners in the information technology (IT) industry as quacks. Its President and Chairman in Council, Prof Charles Uwadia, who spoke during the annual general meeting (AGM) of the group at Lagos Sheraton Hotel, said  the Council has compiled the list of registered members which will be published soon, adding that those whose names are not found on the register will be regarded as IT quacks. He said: “We just finished compiling data of registered members and will be published very soon and if your name is not in that register, you will be regarded as a quack if you are practicing, that is what the law says. “CPN recognise the fact that there are many professionals whose name are not in our register, that is a challenge to us and will be resolved soon, whatever means it will take to achieve that will be put in place.”